    designation: 'National Park',
    parkcode: 'arch',
    id: 3,
    directionsInfo: 'Arches National Park is located in southeast Utah, five miles north of Moab on US 191.\n\nFrom Moab, Utah, drive five miles north on Main Street/US 191. The entrance to the park is on the right.\n\nFrom Interstate 70, take exit 182 (Crescent Junction), then drive south 28 miles on US 191. The entrance to the park is on the left.',
